def":"exercise authority","pos":"verb"},"G2784":{"id":"G2784","lemma":"κηρύσσω","translit":"kērýssō","derivation":"of uncertain affinity;","strongs_def":"to herald (as a public crier), especially divine truth (the gospel)","kjv_def":"preacher(-er), proclaim, publish","pos":"verb","usage":"preach(51x), publish(5x), proclaim(2x), preacher(1x)"},"G2793":{"id":"G2793","lemma":"κινδυνεύω","translit":"kindyneúō","derivation":"from G2794 (κίνδυνος);","strongs_def":"to undergo peril","kjv_def":"be in danger, be (stand) in jeopardy","pos":"verb"},"G2721":{"id":"G2721","lemma":"κατεφίστημι","translit":"katephístēmi","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G2186 (ἐφίστημι);","strongs_def":"to stand over against, i.e. rush upon (assault)","kjv_def":"make insurrection against","pos":"verb"},"G2752":{"id":"G2752","lemma":"κέλευμα","translit":"kéleuma","derivation":"from G2753 (κελεύω);","strongs_def":"a cry of incitement","kjv_def":"shout"},"G2748":{"id":"G2748","lemma":"Κεδρών","translit":"Kedrṓn","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H06939);","strongs_def":"Cedron (i.e. Kidron), a brook near Jerusalem","kjv_def":"Cedron","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Cedron(1x)"},"G2758":{"id":"G2758","lemma":"κενόω","translit":"kenóō","derivation":"from G2756 (κενός);","strongs_def":"to make empty, i.e. (figuratively) to abase, neutralize, falsify","kjv_def":"make (of none effect, of no reputation, void), be in vain","pos":"verb"},"G2766":{"id":"G2766","lemma":"κέραμος","translit":"kéramos","derivation":"probably from the base of G2767 (κεράννυμι) (through the idea of mixing clay and water);","strongs_def":"earthenware, i.e. a tile (by analogy, a thin roof or awning)","kjv_def":"tiling","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"tiling(1x)"},"G2774":{"id":"G2774","lemma":"κεφάλαιον","translit":"kephálaion","derivation":"neuter of a derivative of G2776 (κεφαλή);","strongs_def":"a principal thing, i.e. main point; specially, an amount (of money)","kjv_def":"sum","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"sum(2x)"},"G2720":{"id":"G2720","lemma":"κατευθύνω","translit":"kateuthýnō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G2116 (εὐθύνω);","strongs_def":"to straighten fully, i.e. (figuratively) direct","kjv_def":"guide, direct","pos":"verb","usage":"direct(2x), guide(1x)"},"G2741":{"id":"G2741","lemma":"καυσόω","translit":"kausóō","derivation":"from G2740 (καῦσις);","strongs_def":"to set on fire","kjv_def":"fervent heat"},"G2714":{"id":"G2714","lemma":"κατενώπιον","translit":"katenṓpion","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G1799 (ἐνώπιον);","strongs_def":"directly in front of","kjv_def":"before (the presence of), in the sight of","pos":"adverb","usage":"before(2x)"},"G2757":{"id":"G2757","lemma":"κενοφωνία","translit":"kenophōnía","derivation":"from a presumed compound of G2756 (κενός) and G5456 (φωνή);","strongs_def":"empty sounding, i.e. fruitless discussion","kjv_def":"vain"},"G2716":{"id":"G2716","lemma":"κατεργάζομαι","translit":"katergázomai","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G2038 (ἐργάζομαι);","strongs_def":"to work fully, i.e. accomplish; by implication, to finish, fashion","kjv_def":"cause, to (deed), perform, work (out)","pos":"verb","usage":"work(15x), do(5x), cause(1x)"},"G2788":{"id":"G2788","lemma":"κιθάρα","translit":"kithára","derivation":"of uncertain affinity;","strongs_def":"a lyre","kjv_def":"harp","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"harp(4x)"},"G2768":{"id":"G2768","lemma":"κέρας","translit":"kéras","derivation":"from a primary (the hair of the head);","strongs_def":"a horn (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"horn","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"horn(11x)"},"G2703":{"id":"G2703","lemma":"καταφεύγω","translit":"katapheúgō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G5343 (φεύγω);","strongs_def":"to flee down (away)","kjv_def":"flee","pos":"verb","usage":"flee(2x)"},"G2775":{"id":"G2775","lemma":"κεφαλαιόω","translit":"kephalaióō","derivation":"from the same as G2774 (κεφάλαιον);","strongs_def":"(specially) to strike on the head","kjv_def":"wound in the head","pos":"verb"},"G275